div.p:
GEntle Reader, It was a Luk. 12.3. ſaying of our Saviour: VVhatſoever yee haue spoken in darkneſſe, it ſhal be heard in the light: and that which yee haue ſpoken in the eare in ſecret places, ſhall bee preached on the Houſes. It is now ſome fewe Yeares ſince that being requeſted to afford my help to Leaſt ſome Fitz-Simon ſhould here come in with Neſcio quem, aut quam: (as he did by Sr Edward Hoby: Scripſit Epiſtolam ad M.T.H. neſcio quem, aut quā
                           ) to put him out of doubt it was Ea.
                         ONE of my own Pariſh that was to receaue the Sacrament, & had never receaved it before, I tooke the opportunity of doing my dutie in that kind. To whom afterwards hauing ſent this Letter, & ſome other Lines therewithal concerning the Sacrament: I hold it now fit thus to publiſh them with ſome augmentation, that if ſo be there bee any Other of my Flocke, who deſire to bee inſtructed in like ſort, they may repaire herevnto, and duly meditating therevpon, may not only be the better able to come at all to the holy Sacrament, but the more willing alſo to come often.
